    <h1>
        Lifebyte - Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
        Lifebyte collects and maintains both donator and recipient information as part of
        our ministry services. We only collect information that you provide to us from telephone
        conversations, voice mail, e-mail, or on applications or forms from this Web site.
    </p>
    <p>
        We are a ministry of Colorado Community Church therefore we share information with
        Colorado Community Church so that we can work together to meet your needs. We may
        disclose all of the information we collect, as described above, with Colorado Community
        Church. We share information with nonaffiliated third parties when they are acting
        on our behalf, or acting jointly with us. Where relevant, we may disclose all of
        the information we collect, as described above, to appropriate third parties, including:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>Colorado Community Church</li>
        <li>Denver Rescue Mission </li>
    </ul>
    <p>
        These third parties will be involved in granting or processing your donation or
        computer request on your behalf.
    </p>
    <p>
        We will not disclose nonpublic personal information about you to anyone for the
        purpose of marketing or soliciting products or services other than our own.
    </p>
    <p>
        We are committed to protecting the security and integrity of your information. We
        use SSL which means your information is sent by encrypted text to the server. Please
        do not register on this site with a bank password or company network password! Personally
        identifiable information such as your name, phone number, address, and e-mail address
        are also sent with encrypted text to the server. You always have the option to call
        or e-mail us directly with your information if you desire a higher level of secure
        communication.
    </p>
    <p>
        We do not ask for sensitive information such as social security numbers or credit
        card numbers.
    </p>
    <p>
        Only Lifebyte volunteers are granted access to personally identifiable information.
        Furthermore, all volunteers are kept up-to-date on our security and privacy practices
        any time new policies are added. Our volunteers are notified and/or reminded about
        the importance we place on privacy, and what they can do to ensure your information
        is protected. Finally, our servers will not store personally identifiable information
        about you other than basic phone book information such as your name, address, phone
        number, and e-mail address.
    </p>
    <p>
        Cookies
    </p>
    <p>
        A cookie is a piece of data stored temporarily on your hard drive containing information
        about you. Usage of a cookie is in no way linked to any personally identifiable
        information while on our site. Once you close your browser, the cookie simply terminates.
    </p>
    <p>
        If you reject the cookie, you may still use portions of our site, but will be limited
        in many areas. For example, you will not be able to log in to the member's section.
    </p>
    <p>
        Once again we thank you for sharing your personal information with us for the purpose
        of furthering our ministry.
    </p>
    <p>
        The policies and practices described in this disclosure are subject to change, but
        we will communicate any significant changes to you as required by applicable law.
    </p>
